File: President Cyril Ramaphosa.Â GCIS JOHANNESBURG - South Africa will move to lockdown alert level two from Monday. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement following a cabinet meeting. The decision comes in light of the recent proportion of Covid-19 positive tests, among others. LIVESTREAM: President Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the nation Over the last 7 days, there has been an average of 3745 daily new infections. The nationwide curfew hours have also been tightened, and it will start at 11pm and end at 4am.